able humilitie one to an other. Ioan. 13. 12. Wherefore no more in this then in any other matter doe we take any light, out of the bookes and doings of those owles, that flye in the darkenes of mens traditions, but onely out of the lawe of God which is a light vnto our steps, and a lanterne vnto our feete, that we neede not like apes counterfeit externall toyes as they doe, but being followers of God as wellbeloued children, we may walke in loue as Christ hath loued vs, and so fa
